.\" CT Programming Language Manual
.TH CT 1 "2024-01-01" "1.0" "CT Programming Language"

.SH NAME
ct \- CT programming language interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ct
[options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
CT is a simple, lightweight scripting language interpreter written in C.
It supports variables, arithmetic operations, loops, conditionals, and
built-in mathematical functions.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display help information and exit.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Display version information and exit.
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-eval\fR \fIcode\fR
Execute the given code string.
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR \fIfile\fR
Execute the specified CT file.

.SH USAGE

.SS Interactive Mode
When called without arguments, ct enters interactive mode:
.PP
.RS
$ ct
> let x = 10
> print x
10
> exit
.RE

.SS File Execution
Execute a CT script file:
.PP
.RS
$ ct script.ct
.RE

.SS One-liner
Execute code directly from command line:
.PP
.RS
$ ct -e "print 1+2+3"
6
.RE

.SH LANGUAGE SYNTAX

.SS Variables
.RS
let x = 10
let y = 20
let z = x + y
.RE

.SS Print
.RS
print "Hello World"
print x + y * 2
.RE

.SS Arithmetic Operators
.RS
+   addition
-   subtraction
*   multiplication
/   division
( ) parentheses for grouping
.RE

.SS Loops (while)
.RS
let i = 1
while i <= 10 {
    print i
    let i = i + 1
}
.RE

.SS Conditionals (if)
.RS
if x > 10 {
    print "greater"
}
.RE

.SS Built-in Functions
.RS
sin(x)   - sine of x
cos(x)   - cosine of x
sqrt(x)  - square root of x
abs(x)   - absolute value of x
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES

.SS Calculate sum from 1 to 100
.RS
$ ct -e "let s=0;let i=1;while i<=100{let s=s+i;let i=i+1};print s"
5050
.RE

.SS Fibonacci sequence
.RS
$ cat fib.ct
let a = 0
let b = 1
let i = 0
while i < 20 {
    print a
    let fib = a + b
    let a = b
    let b = fib
    let i = i + 1
}
$ ct fib.ct
.RE

.SS Prime numbers within 100
.RS
$ cat prime.ct
let n = 2
while n <= 100 {
    let is_prime = 1
    let i = 2
    while i * i <= n {
        if n % i == 0 {
            let is_prime = 0
        }
        let i = i + 1
    }
    if is_prime {
        print n
    }
    let n = n + 1
}
$ ct prime.ct
.RE

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/ct
The CT interpreter binary.
.TP
.I /usr/local/share/ct/lib/
Standard library files.
.TP
.I ~/.ct_history
Command history in interactive mode.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
Directory containing the ct executable should be in your PATH.

